5:
Heh, today's request went well.
Planning was easy, and the rewards
weren't bad, either.
8:
Indeed. Perhaps we should spend
the rest of the afternoon handling
easy tasks in the Kaleidoscope.
10:
Veggies! Come get your veggies!
Freshly picked just this morning!
14:
Make sure you check out the carrots
today! They're sweet, fresh, and
super delicious!
22:
Oh, hey! I haven't seen you since the
Palpebra Cup. Have you all been
doing well?
28: Yes. I'm glad you look well, too.
32: That's me. I'm always full of energy!
37:
Still, I didn't think I'd see you in
Palpebra.
41:
Hehe! I have a day off from training
today, so I came here to have fun!
46:
B-but... Are you not simply selling
vegetables?
55:
This young lady, here? She saved
me, you know.
57:
I couldn't move because my back
was flaring up again, so she carried
all of my stuff for me. She even
decided to help me with my
vegetable stand...
61:
Umamusume are not only fast, but
strong, too! It wasn't any trouble!
64:
I see. Even still, I'd say stopping to
help someone in need like this
makes you quite special.
73:
O-oh, you think so? Hehe, that's
kinda embarrassing...
78:
Well then, are we all settled on our
plans for this afternoon?
91:
Veggies! Get your veggies here!
They go great in a soup or side dish!
96: A-are you sure about this, everyone?
99:
Well, we weren't really sure what to
do for the rest of the day anyway.
103:
This isn't a bad way to spend an
afternoon.
110:
Ah, welcome! Looking for some fresh
veggies?
118:
Looks like everything's been sold.
Glad it all worked out!
121:
Thank you very much, dear. And a
big thanks to your friends, too.
124:
No trouble at all! It was nice getting
to spend the day like this—
129:
Heh-heh. My back's feeling much
better, and now all I need to do is
clean up. I can manage on my own
now.
131:
Here's your pay. It isn't much, but
you should be able to afford
something nice to eat with all your
friends.
135: Huh?! Oh, no, I can't accept this!
138:
It's fine, just take it. I want you to
have this.
140:
Oh. Are you leaving already? In that
case, have some of my cookies.
They're just the ones I didn't sell
today, but I hope you'll like them.
142:
Oh! Then take some skewers of
mine, too! I don't wanna brag, but
they're pretty great!
154:
I think it makes sense. They're drawn
to her personality.
158: We could learn a lot from her.
166:
Mmm, so tasty! Nothing beats a nice
meal after a hard day's work!
169:
Th-that's good to hear, but... I can
hardly believe how much you just
put down...
172:
Ah... Right. You don't have
Umamusume in your world...
180:
That makes sense, given how fast
you run.
184:
Well... Even when compared to the
others, I can eat quite a lot...
188:
Ah, excuse me! I'd like another one
of these, please!
193:
I think it's great, though. You train
hard every day and compete in
races. You're just enjoying a day off,
right?
197:
Mmm... Yes. There are a lot of tough
things I need to do.
200:
But I also have a lot of fun, and there
are plenty of things I get to do that
make me happy!
203:
Besides, my dream is to become the
top Umamusume in Japan! I can't
lose!
212:
Hey. If you wouldn't mind, would you
let us help you with that?
214:
We aren't pros, of course, and we
can't help with training or anything,
but...
217:
If you're looking for a change of
pace on one of your days off, I'm
sure we can help you out.
228:
This is Starview Village. We look at
other worlds from here.
232:
We use the World Flipper to travel to
many different worlds.
237:
I think this could be a great way for
you to take your mind off things
when you're having a hard time...
But what do you think?
243:
...Yes! That would be wonderful for
me!
252:
Thank you! Once again, I look
forward to working together with
you all!
259: I'm not going to lose the next race!
